sn35.210-212:3.1: 210–212 The Interior and What’s Not-Self in the Three Times
sn35.210-212:4.1: “Mendicants, in the past … future … present the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind are not-self.
sn35.210-212:4.2: And what’s not-self should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ …”
